<Page title="About" description="About Akhmad Reiza Armando — software engineer, husband, and dad.">
  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Who I am</h2>
    <p>
      I'm a software engineer, a husband, and a dad. I live in Indonesia with my wife and kids,
      and I spend most of my non-work hours with them — at the dinner table, on weekend trips,
      or looking for the next place worth eating at.
    </p>

    <h2>What I do</h2>
    <p>
      I work on backend systems with a focus on distributed systems and developer tooling.
      I like understanding how things work under the hood and building things that are simple,
      reliable, and last.
    </p>

    <h2>Outside work</h2>
    <p>
      Food is a serious hobby. I believe a city is best understood through its food, which is a
      convenient excuse to travel. When we do travel as a family, I try to plan the restaurant
      list before the itinerary.
    </p>

    <h2>This site</h2>
    <p>
      I write here about software, food, and travel — whatever I'm thinking about or just figured
      out. No fixed schedule, no niche. Just things I'd want to read myself.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Find me on <a href="https://github.com/akhmadreiza">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Page>
